.CENTER;TAPES
.CENTER;-----
.SKIP 1
.FILL.JUST
                FILE TAPES:
.SKIP 1
                        NEW TAPES PLUS ANY TAPE WITH LESS THAN
                35 ERRORS IS CONSIDERED A FILE TAPE.
.SKIP 1
                        ALLFILE TAPES AND NEW TAPES ARE SIGNED OUT
                        ON THE "MAGTAPE LOGOUT SHEET" ON TOP OF THE
                        TABLE IN THE TAPE LIBRARY.  (SEE APPENDIX
                        II)
.SKIP 1
                        THE FILE TAPE LOGOUT SHEETS SHOULD 
                BE KEPT ON FILE FOR AT LEAST 3 MONTHS.  WITH THIS
                LOGOUT SHEET WE GET A GENERAL IDEA OF WHERE THE 
                TAPES ARE GOING.
.SKIP 1
                SCRATCH TAPES:
.SKIP 1
                        THESE ARE ANY TAPES WITH 35 WRITE ERRORS OR 
                LESS.  TAPES WITH MORE THAN 35 WRITE ERRORS ARE TO BE
                CYCLED OUT FOR CERTIFICATION.
.SKIP 1
.NOFILL.NOJUST
.CENTER;RECORDS
.CENTER;-------
.SKIP 1
.FILL.JUST
                        ALWAYS KEEP A COPY OF THE BATCH REQUEST 
                WHEN ADDING, RELEASING, OR TRANSFERRING TAPES.
                THESE PPR COPIES MUST BE RETAINED FOR AT LEAST
                6 MONTHS.  ALWAYS WRITE TID AND TRP NUMBER ON YOUR COPY.
.SKIP 1
                        THE TAPE CHECK-OUT LOG FOR BACK UP TAPES,
                ALLFILE TAPES, OR CUSTOMER TAPES MUST BE  KEPT FOR A
                PERIOD OF 4 - 6 MONTHS.
.SKIP 1
