.INDEX ADDING TAPES
.CENTER;ADDING TAPES
.CENTER;------------
.SKIP 1
.FILL.JUST
1.  PROCEDURES FOR ADDING TAPES TO THE "TAPELIB" DATA-BASE ARE COVERED
IN MINI-MANUAL _#1A.  IN ADDITION TO THE INSTRUCTIONS CONTAINED IN THIS
MANUAL, THE FOLLOWING SHOULD BE CHECKED BEFORE ADDING ANY TAPE
TO THE LIBRARY.  EVERY OPERATOR, WHO "ADDS" OR "RELEASES" A TAPE, IS
REQUIRED TO COMPLETE THE APPROPRIATE FORM.  IF THESE FORMS ARE UNAVAILABLE,
THEY CAN BE LISTED OUT ON TTY PAPER FROM THE DIRECTORY OF FREMONTDOC.  FILENAMES
ARE:  "ADDTAP.MEM" AND "RELTAP.MEM".
.SKIP 1
.LM 11
A.  READ BATCH REQUEST TO ASCERTAIN IF TAPE(S) ARE TO BE ADDED TO LIBRARY.
.SKIP 1
B.  IF TAPE(S) ARE TO BE ADDED, DO YOU HAVE THE ORIGINAL BATCH REQUEST WITH
ALL HARDCOPY?
.SKIP 1
C.  IS THERE A TAPE DIRECTORY WITH EACH TAPE?  THE ONLY TIME YOU WON'T
HAVE A DIRECTORY IS WHEN FILES WERE "MAGCON" TO TAPE.
.LM 7
.NOTE
EACH TAPE SHOULD BE MOUNTED SEPARATELY WHEN PRINTING A DIRECTORY.  TAPE
DIRECTORY HEADERS SHOULD NOT START IN THE MIDDLE OF A PAGE IF MORE THAN
ONE TAPE IS TO BE ADDED.
.END NOTE
.LM 11
D.  DID YOU MARK THE "TRP" AND "TID" NUMBERS ON THE TAPE DIRECTORY AND
BATCH REQUEST AS YOU ENTERED THE TAPE(S) IN LIBRARY?
.SKIP 1
.LM 7
2.  AFTER THE TAPE(S) ARE ADDED TO THE LIBRARY, TEAR OFF YOUR HARDCOPY
FROM THE TERMINAL AND DO THE FOLLOWING:
.SKIP 1
.LM 11
A.  CUT OUT YOUR FIRST LABEL AND SCOTCH-TAPE ALL FOUR (4) SIDES TO THE
TAPE(S).  IF THERE ARE ANY LABELS ON THE TAPE - LEAVE THEM ON THE TAPE.
DO THIS WITH EACH TAPE.
.SKIP 1
B.  AFTER ALL TAPE(S) ARE LABELED, FILE THE TAPE DIRECTORY IN THE "TAPE
DIRECTORY" FILE CABINET IN THE APPROPRIATE FOLDER.
.SKIP 1
C.  TAKE THE TAPE(S) OVER TO THE TAPE RACK AND REMOVE THE "BLANK" STRAP
AND PUT THE STRAP WITH THE "TRP" ON IT AND HANG IT IN ITS PROPER PLACE.
HANG THE "BLANK" STRAP WITH THE OTHER BLANK STRAPS.
.SKIP 1
D.  AFTER COMPLETING THE ABOVE, SEND MAIL TO THE USER, GIVING "TID"
NUMBERS ONLY EVEN IF BATCH REQUEST ASKS FOR BOTH.
.SKIP 1
E.  MAKE A COPY OF THE BATCH REQUEST FOR THE TAPE LIBRARIAN.  GIVE ORIGINAL
REQUEST BACK TO "BATCH CONTROLLER" FOR "QA".
.SKIP 1
F.  ENTER THE PPR INTO BCHARGE AS A "JOB TYPE _#4".  CHARGE AS ONE (1)
FILE PER TAPE.
.PAGE
