.INDEX RELEASING TAPES
.INDEX RELEASED/RETURNED TO USER
.NOFILL.NOJUST
.CENTER;RELEASING TAPES
.CENTER;---------------
.SKIP 1
.FILL.JUST
1.  TAPES ARE RELEASED FROM THE TAPE LIBRARY WHEN REQUESTED BY THE OWNER
OF THE TAPE BY SUBMITTING A BATCH REQUEST.  THE BATCH REQUEST SHOULD CONTAIN
INSTRUCTIONS AS TO THE DISPOSITION OF THE TAPE.  IF IT DOESN'T, NO TAPE
IS RELEASED UNTIL THIS INFORMATION IS OBTAINED FROM THE PERSON WHO
SUBMITTED THE REQUEST.
.SKIP 1
2.  TAPES ARE DISPOSED OF IN SEVERAL WAYS: RELEASED AND RETURNED
TO USER; OR, RELEASED AND SCRATCHED.
.SKIP 1
3.  BEFORE A TAPE IS RELEASED, CERTAIN PROCEDURES MUST BE PERFORMED FIRST.
THESE PROCEDURES ARE LISTED BELOW.
.SKIP 1
.LM 11
A.  RELEASED AND RETURNED TO USER.
.SKIP 1
.LM 15
(1)  DO YOU HAVE THE CORRECT TAPE?
.SKIP 1
(2)  DO THE "TID'S" MATCH?  COMPARE BATCH REQUEST
AGAINST TAPE LABEL.
.SKIP 1
(3)  IF APPLICABLE, DID YOU PULL "TAPE" DIRECTORY FROM
TAPE DIRECTORY CABINET?  IS IT THE CORRECT DIRECTORY?
.SKIP 1
(4)  DID YOU STAMP THE "TAPE LABEL" AND THE "BATCH"
REQUEST WITH THE "RELEASED FROM BT TYMNET" RUBBER
STAMP OR "TRANSFERRED" RUBBER STAMP?
.SKIP 1
(5)  DID YOU REMOVE THE CURRENT "TAPE STRAP" FROM TAPE
AND PUT A "BLANK" TAPE STRAP ON TAPE?
.SKIP 1
(6)  DID YOU PUT THE STRAP YOU REMOVED ABOVE BACK IN THE
"TRP" POSITION ON TAPE RACK?
.SKIP 1
(7)  IS THERE A RUBBER "HOLD-DOWN" ON TAPE?
.SKIP 1
(8)  DID YOU LOG THE TAPE OUT IN THE "TAPE RELEASED" LOG?  (SEE APPENDIX <III)
.PAGE
(9)  DID YOU PROVIDE A COPY OF THE BATCH REQUEST
FOR THE TAPE LIBRARIAN?
.SKIP 1
(10) DID YOU LOG THE TAPE OUT IN THE "DAILY TAPE" CHECK
OUT LOG AND "STAMP" IT AS BEING "RELEASED" OR "TRANSFERRED"?
(SEE APPENDIX <IV)
.SKIP 1
(11) DID YOU SEND MAIL AND ENTER THE BATCH REQUEST INTO BCHARGE?
CHARGE AS A JOB TYPE _#4.  1 TAPE = 1 FILE, 2 TAPES = 2 FILES, ETC.
.SKIP 1
(12) BEFORE TAKING THE TAPE TO DISTRIBUTION FOR MAILING, DID YOU:
.SKIP 1
.LM 20
(A) MAKE TWO (2) COPIES OF THE BATCH
REQUEST?
.SKIP 1
(B) TAPE A COPY OF THE BATCH REQUEST TO THE TAPE
WITH DIRECTORY?
.SKIP 1
.LM 11
.INDEX RELEASED AND SCRATCHED
B.  RELEASED AND SCRATCHED.
.SKIP 1
.LM 15
(1)  SEE PARAGRAPH 3.A(1) THROUGH 3.A(10).
.SKIP 1
(2)  DID YOU MAKE UP A "HOLD AND DESTROY" FORM
AND ATTACH IT TO TAPE WITH DIRECTORY?
.SKIP 1
(3)  DID YOU INDICATE THE TAPE TO BE SCRATCHED IN
FORTY-FIVE (45) DAYS?
.SKIP 1
(4)  DID YOU PLACE IT IN THE "HOLD AND DESTROY"
CABINET?
.SKIP 1
(5) DID YOU SEND MAIL AND VOID THE REQUEST IN BCHARGE?
CHARGE AS A JOB TYPE _#4.  1 TAPE = 1 FILE, 2 TAPES = 2 FILES, ETC.
.SKIP 1
(6) DID YOU MAKE COPIES OF THE BATCH REQUEST FOR THE TAPE LIBRARIAN?
.PAGE
