.INDEX OFF-SITE STORAGE
.FILL.JUST
.CENTER
<OFF-SITE <STORAGE <SYSTEM
.CENTER
-------- ------- ------
.PARA
^THE COMPUTER CENTER IS THE CENTRALIZED CONTROL AREA FOR THE DATA
SERVICES OFFERED BY ^BT TYMNET: IT IS ON THE COMPUTERS WHERE ALL PROGRAMS
APPLICATIONS AND INFORMATION FILES ARE PROCESSED; WHERE ALL THE USER'S
WORK EFFORTS ARE CREATED, MAINTAINED, UPDATED, DISTRIBUTED AND SO ON.
^THIS TREMENDOUS IMPORTANCE BRINGS WITH IT A TREMENDOUS REQUIREMENT FOR
SECURITY. 
.PARA
^PROGRAMS AND APPLICATIONS ARE PRODUCTS WHICH MUST BE SAFEGUARDED  SO
THEY ARE AVAILABLE TO THE USER AS ADVERTISED.
^ALL WORK EFFORTS BY THE USER MUST BE SECURED SINCE MUCH OF THE DATA
IS VITAL TO THE USER'S COMPANY, IT'S CASH FLOW, PAYROLL, INVENTORY, ETC.
^AS ONE LEVEL OF PRECAUTION, OPERATIONS MAINTAINS DUPLICATE BACKUP STORAGE
OF THE COMPUTER'S FILES ON MAGNETIC TAPES. 
^THESE ARE KEPT 'OFF-LINE' AS INSURANCE AGAINST LOSS OF ON-LINE DATA.
.PARA
^BUT THE COMPUTER CENTER ITSELF IS VULNERABLE. 
^BECAUSE OF THE VITAL IMPORTANCE OF DATA GENERATED IN THE COMPUTER CENTER
AN ADDITIONAL LEVEL OF BACKUP SECURITY HAS BEEN ESTABLISHED: THE
<ARCUS 'OFF-SITE' VITAL RECORDS PROTECTION SYSTEM.
^PERIODICALLY, RECENT COPIES OF PROGRAMS, APPLICATIONS AND USER DATA
IN THE FORM OF TAPES, WILL BE PLACED IN METAL CONTAINERS.
^THESE MEDIA CONTAINERS WILL BE LOCKED AND
STORED IN A SECURE ENVIRONMENT LOCATED SOME DISTANCE FROM THE COMPUTER
CENTER.
^THIS PROVIDES INSURANCE AGAINST LOSS OF DATA DUE TO A NATURAL OR
PLANNED DISASTER TO THE COMPUTER CENTER ITSELF.
.PARA
^FOR ^BAY ^AREA COMPUTER CENTERS, THIS OFF LINE BACKUP WILL BE MAINTAINED
IN VAULTS IN ^UNION ^CITY.
^THIS SECTION OUTLINES THE ROTATION SCHEDULE TO AND FROM <ARCUS, AND
DESCRIBE THE PROCEDURES THAT ARE TO BE USED FOR ACCESSING DATA SHOULD
IMMEDIATE RETURN BE NECESSARY.
.PAGE
^^
.SKIP 1
.INDEX <ASP FILE ROTATION
.CENTER
ASP TAPE ROTATION
.LM 7
.NOTE
DO NOT MIX ASP TAPES WITH OTHER SYSTEM TAPES.
.END NOTE
        1) FREMONT COMPUTER CENTER OFF-SITE STORAGE IS IN 
           CONTAINERS EACH CONTAINING HOWEVER MANY TAPES THERE ARE 
           FOR ONE TYMCOM-X ASP SET.
.SKIP 1
        2) FOR FREMONT THIS IS THE SET BEFORE THE SET WE WRITE ON.
           THIS SET IS THE EQUIVALENT TO A PACKCOPY SET AND SHOULD
           ONLY BE USED FOR FILE SYSTEM REBUILDS UNLESS OTHERWISE
           AUTHORIZED BY THE SHIFT SUPERVISOR OR OPERATIONS MANAGER.
.NOTE
IF THE 'ASP DUMP' IS STARTED, AND THEN FOR SOME REASON IT HAD TO BE
CANCELLED, THIS SET STAYS AT THE CENTER AND IS USED AGAIN FOR THE NEXT
SCHEDULED DUMP.  YOU "NEVER" WRITE OVER THE "OLDEST" SET UNTIL YOU HAVE
A GOOD DUMP.  THIS SET WOULD BE USED IF A 'REBUILD' SHOULD OCCUR.
.END NOTE
        3) ARCUS WILL SEND A DELIVERY TRUCK EVERY TUESDAY AND THURSDAY RETURNING
           THE CONTAINERS DUE BACK AT THE CENTER AND
           PICK UP THE CONTAINERS DUE TO GO OUT.  THESE MUST BE
           READY BY 0800 THE DAY THEY ARE TO BE RETURNED.
.SKIP 1
        4) A KEY FOR THE CANNISTERS WILL BE KEPT ON THE KEY RING IN
           THE BATCH OFFICE.  EVERY SUPERVISOR ALSO HAS A KEY.
.SKIP 1
        5) THE APPROPRIATE AUTHORIZATION FORM MUST BE FILLED OUT
           BY SOMEONE WITH AN ARCUS I.D. CARD.
.SKIP 1
        6) THE CUSTOMER COPY SHOULD BE FILED IN THE ARCUS BOOK
           LOCATED ON TAPE LIBRARIAN'S DESK.
           ON DELIVERY YOU'LL RECEIVE A RECEIPT WHICH IS FILED
           WITH THE PICKUP FORM.
.SKIP 1
.INDEX UNSCHEDULED <ASP TAPE RETURN
.CENTER
UNSCHEDULED ASP TAPE RETURN
.SKIP 1
        1) IF DATA IS NEEDED FROM ARCUS STORAGE (IN OTHER WORDS
           YOU NEED THIS SET OF TAPES TO DO A FILE SYSTEM REBUILD) THEN
           CHECK THE ARCUS BOOK TO DETERMINE THE  CONTAINER
           NUMBER WHICH STORES THE DATA. WHEN YOU'VE FOUND THE
           APPROPRIATE SHEET NOTE THE CONTAINER NUMBER AND THE 
           SCHEDULED RETURN DATE.
.SKIP 1
        2) CALL ARCUS AT:       *** 9-489-5100 ***
.SKIP 1
        3) GIVE YOUR ARCUS I.D. NUMBER AND BT TYMNET'S ACCOUNT
           NUMBER:              *** 1630 ***
.SKIP 1
        4) GIVE THE CONTAINER NUMBERS YOU NEED AND THE SCHEDULED
           RETURN DATE FROM THE PICKUP AUTHORIZATION FORM.
.SKIP 1
        5) RECORD THE TIME THE CALL TO ARCUS WAS INITIATED TO KEEP
           TRACK OF THE TURNAROUND TIME.
.SKIP 1
        6) DETERMINE FROM THE SHIFT SUPERVISOR THE NECESSITY OF RETAINING
           CANISTERS FURTHER INHOUSE.  IF NO LONGER NEEDED, THEY
           WILL BE RETURNED TO ARCUS WITH THE NEXT PICKUP TO FULFILL
           THE ORIGINAL RETENTION.
           REMEMBER THAT ONLY ENTIRE CONTAINER(S) WILL BE
           RETURNED. ARCUS WILL NEVER OPEN A CONTAINER AND
           RETURN ONLY PART OF IT'S CONTENTS. THE REQUESTED
           CANISTER(S) SHOULD ARRIVE IN APPROXIMATELY 2 HOURS.
.PAGE
.INDEX PREPARING TAPES FOR SHIPMENT
.CENTER;PREPARING TAPES FOR SHIPMENT
.CENTER;----------------------------
.SKIP 1
.FILL.JUST
.LM 7
ARCUS PROVIDES LOCKING METAL CONTAINERS TO HOUSE THE TAPES.  OUR CONTRACT
WITH THEM SPECIFIES DAILY PICKUP, TUESDAY AND THURSDAY, AND STORAGE
OF THESE CONTAINERS.
.SKIP 1
ASP TAPES ARE TO BE COLLECTED FOR TRANSFER TO ARCUS BY THE PDP-10
GRAVESHIFT OPERATOR DESIGNATED BY SHIFT SUPERVISOR.
CONTAINERS MUST BE AT THE LOADING DOCK BY 0800 MONDAY (FOLLOWING DUMP), PER
OUR AGREEMENT.  AN "ARCUS PICKUP AUTHORIZATION FORM" MUST BE
COMPLETED TO ACCOMPANY THE CONTAINERS FOR EACH PICKUP.
.SKIP 1
OUTLINED BELOW IS THE PROCEDURE FOR FILLING OUT THE FORM.
.SKIP 1
.LM 11
.NOFILL.NOJUST
I.  FORM HEADING.
.SKIP 1
.LM 15
A.  ACCOUNT NO. - BT TYMNET ACCOUNT NO:  1630.
.SKIP 1
B.  CUSTOMER NAME:  YOUR "ARCUS" ID NO.
.SKIP 1
C.  DATE:  CURRENT DATE A MM/DD/YY.
.SKIP 1
D.  TIME:  TIME OF PICKUP IN MILITARY NOTATION TO BE RECORDED
           IN THE PRESENCE OF THE "ARCUS" MESSENGER BY THE
           PDP-10 OPERATOR DESIGNATED OR LOADING DOCK CLERK.
.SKIP 1
E.  RECEIVED BY:  SIGNATURE OF "ARCUS" MESSENGER.
.SKIP 1
F.  RECEIVED FROM:  SIGNATURE OF PDP-10 OPERATOR OR CLERK
                    PRESENT AT PICKUP TIME.
.SKIP 1
G.  RECORD (AS A HEADING):  BI-WEEKLY, OR WEEKLY, ABOVE THE
                            DESCRIPTION AREA FOR TAPES SENT.
.SKIP 1
.LM 11
II.  FORM CONTENTS
.SKIP 1
.LM 15
A.  NUMBER:  "ARCUS" CONTAINER NUMBER(S).
.SKIP 1
B.  RETURN DATE:  DATE AS MM/DD/YY TAPES ARE TO BE DELIVERED
                  BACK TO FREMONT OPERATIONS.
.SKIP 1
C.  DESCRIPTION:  CANISTER NUMBER AND CORRESPONDING TAPE
                  NUMBER(S) OF ALL (9) NINE TAPES INSIDE THE
                  CONTAINER.
.PAGE
.LM 7
.FILL.JUST
USE THE ASP STATUS REPORT AND THE ASP RECORD LOG TO FIND
THE CORRECT SET OF TAPES TO SEND TO "ARCUS".  CHECK WITH SHIFT
SUPERVIISOR ABOUT ANY ASP DUMPS NOT RUN.
.SKIP 1
AFTER PLACING ALL TAPES IN THE CONTAINERS, LOCK EACH ONE.  TAKE THEM,
TOGETHER WITH THE COMPLETED "ARCUS PICKUP AUTHORIZATION FORM", TO THE
LOADING DOCK.  BOTH THE ORGINAL AND THE COPY OF THE FORM MUST REMAIN
WITH THE CONTAINERS UNTIL THE "ARCUS" MESSENGER HAS SIGNED FOR AND
RECEIVED THEM.  HE WILL RETAIN THE COPY; THE ORIGINAL WILL BE RETAINED
FOR PCKUP BY THE OPERATOR DESIGNATED, WHO WILL INSERT IT IN THE "ARCUS"
BINDER ON THE TAPE LIBRARIANS DESK.  IT WILL REMAIN THERE WITH ANY OTHER
FORMS SHOWING OUTSTANDING CONTAINERS.
.SKIP 1
IF ALL CANNISTERS DUE BACK ARE NOT RECEIVED, NOTIFY ARCUS IMMEDIATELY OF
CANNISTER NUMBERS THAT NEED TO BE RETURNED.  ENTIRE SETS MUST BE RETURNED.
.SKIP 1
SERIAL NUMBERS OF BOXES MUST BE CHECKED AGAINST RECEIPT LOG WHEN THEY
FIRST ARRIVE.  IF A DISCREPANCY SHOULD ARISE - LET DRIVER KNOW BEFORE HE LEAVES
THE CENTER.
.PAGE
.INDEX MAGNETIC BOARD
.CENTER;MAGNETIC BOARD
.CENTER;--------------
THE PURPOSE OF THE MAGBOARD IS TO KEEP ALL SHIFTS INFORMED OF THE ROUTINES
TO BE PERFORMED DURING A 24 HOUR DAY ON CERTAIN SYSTEMS.
.SKIP 1
THE DAYSHIFT SUPERVISOR, OR HIS DESIGNATED REPRESENTATIVE, WILL UPDATE THE BOARD
ON A DAILY BASIS.  NO ONE ELSE IS AUTHORIZED TO CHANGE ANYTHING ONCE IT IS
SCHEDULED, UNLESS DIRECTED TO DO SO BY ONE OF THE ABOVE.
.SKIP 1
IT IS EACH OPERATORS RESPONSIBILITY TO CHECK THIS BOARD AT THE
BEGINNING OF HIS/HER SHIFT TO FIND OUT WHAT IS TO BE PERFORMED ON THE
SYSTEMS.
.SKIP 1
A "BLACK DOT" SHOULD BE PLACED NEXT TO THE EVENT AFTER IT HAS BEEN
COMPLETED BY THE OPERATOR WHO IS THE SYSTEM QUALITY CONTROLLER.
.PAGE
.INDEX CLEANING TAPES
.CENTER;PROCEDURES FOR CLEANING AND RECERTIFYING TAPES
.CENTER;----------------------------------------------
.SKIP 1
.LM 0
.LM 14
.FILL.JUST
1.  GATHER TAPES TO BE SCRATCHED AND PLACE ON CART.
.SKIP 1
2.  GO OVER TO MVS AND VM AREA.
.SKIP 1
3.  OBSERVE AREA, IF THERE ARE IBM TAPES LYING AROUND CHECK WITH
MVS AND VM LIBRARIAN ON THE STATUS.  START OUT WITH ORDERLY AREA.
.SKIP 1
4.  CLEAN MACHINE BEFORE USE AND AFTER EVERY FOURTH TAPE AND ALSO
AT THE END OF COMPLETE USE.
.SKIP 1
5.  LOAD TAPE.
.SKIP 1
6.  AFTER TAPE IS FINISHED, PLACE RELIABILITY LABEL ON BACK WITH
INFORMATION FILLED IN.
.SKIP 1
7.  IF TAPE HAS ANY PHYSICAL DAMAGE THROW IT AWAY ONLY IF THE DAMAGE
IS MORE THAN 400' FROM EITHER END.  IF TAPE HAS 35 OR MORE WRITE CHECK ERRORS
BOX UP AND SEND OFF-SITE FOR CERTIFICATION.
.SKIP 1
.LM 0
.LM 14
8.  TAPES TO BE KEPT:
.SKIP 1
.LM 0
.LM 18
A.  PLACE GROMMET ON TAPE.
.SKIP 1
B.  ONLY USE STRAPS THAT SAY 'WRIGHT LINE' ON THEM.
.SKIP 1
C.  CLEAN OFF ALL EVIDENCE OF PREVIOUS LABELS OR ANY WRITING ON TAPE
STRAP.
.SKIP 1
.LM 0
.LM 7
.NOFILL.NOJUST
.CENTER;UPON COMPLETION
.CENTER;---------------
.SKIP 1
.LM 0
.LM 14
.FILL.JUST
1.  THROW OUT ANY TAPES WITH PHYSICAL ERRORS IN DUMPSTER IN LOADING
DOCK AREA.
.SKIP 1
2.  PLACE THE GOOD TAPES ON RACK WHERE SPECIFIED FOR SCRATCH TAPES IN
PDP-10 TAPE LIBRARY.
.SKIP 1
3.  BE SURE YOU HAVE NOT LEFT ANY PDP-10 TAPES OR STRAPS IN THE MVS AND
VM AREA.
